Package: orderbook
Type: Package
Title: Orderbook: A package for working with limit orders
Depends: R (>= 2.11.0), methods, lattice, grid
Version: 1.1
Date: 2010-08-25
Author: Andrew Liu, David Kane
Maintainer: Andrew Liu <Andrew.T.Liu@williams.edu>
Description: Functions for working with orderbook data. An electronic
	     limit order book is a collection of limit orders, most
	     commonly seen at stock exchanges. A limit order is an
	     offer to buy or sell stock at a specific price. The set
	     of all limit orders for a give stock make up the
	     orderbook. The orderbook package provides tools for
	     creating objects of class orderbook as well as
	     printing/plotting/summarizing those orderbooks. See the
	     package vignette for more details.
License: GPL (>= 2)
LazyLoad: yes
ZipData: No
Repository/R-Forge/Project: limitob
